---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use | Pizza & Friends"
  description="Terms for using the Pizza & Friends community site."
>
  <main id="main-content" class="legal-page">
    <a href="/" class="legal-back">&larr; Home</a>

    <header class="legal-header">
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="legal-lede">
        Last updated: July 4, 2026. By using joinpizza.fun you agree to these terms.
      </p>
    </header>

    <article class="legal-body">
      <section>
        <h2>About the site</h2>
        <p>
          Pizza &amp; Friends is an informal tech-and-dinner community run by volunteers.
          This website is a brochure for events and links — not a platform with hosted user
          accounts.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Community conduct</h2>
        <p>
          Real-world meetups and Discord conversations have their own community norms.
          Be respectful. Harassment, spam, or abuse may result in removal from community spaces.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Content and photos</h2>
        <p>
          Event photos and descriptions are shared to celebrate the community. Do not reuse
          them to misrepresent the group or impersonate organizers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Acceptable use of this site</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Do not attempt to disrupt hosting or probe for vulnerabilities.</li>
          <li>Do not scrape the site aggressively or republish it as a commercial product.</li>
          <li>External links are provided as-is; we are not responsible for third-party sites.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          The site is provided "as is." Event details may change. Organizers are not liable
          for decisions you make based on information here.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          These terms may be updated. Continued use after changes are posted constitutes
          acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 40rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 5rem;
  }

  .legal-back {
    font-family: var(--font-geist-sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted, #6b6560);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .legal-back:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .legal-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-libre-baskerville);
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .legal-lede {
    font-family: var(--font-geist-sans);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-muted, #6b6560);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .legal-body section {
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .legal-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-libre-baskerville);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-body p,
  .legal-body li {
    font-family: var(--font-geist-sans);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-muted, #6b6560);
  }

  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }
</style>
